Here's a simple algorithm to find the common elements in two arrays without using extra data structures:


    function findCommonElements(arr1, arr2) {
        const set1 = new Set(arr1);
        const set2 = new Set(arr2);
        const commonElements = [...set1.values()].filter(commonElement => {
            return [...set2].includes(commonElement);
        });
        return commonElements;
    }


The function takes two arrays as input, creates two sets using the arrays as the keys, and then filters the elements of the first set to find the common elements in both arrays. The `filter()` method is used to iterate over the elements of the first set and check if they exist in the second set using the `includes()` method. Finally, the common elements are returned as an array.
